+# Release v0.4.0 — Money Arithmetic + Ruled Ledger Visual v2
+
+**Date:** 2026-05-28
+**Bump:** MINOR (`0.3.0 → 0.4.0`)
+**Tag:** `v0.4.0` → `300e220`
+
+## Why this version
+
+Backward-compatible feature additions, **no breaking changes** since `0.3.0`.
+Under `0.x` semantic versioning a feature release increments the **minor**, so
+this lands as `0.4.0`. The bump is derived from the merged history, not guessed:
+`git log v0.3.0..HEAD` is two `feat` commits (ADR 0003 money arithmetic; visual
+v2 identity) plus one asset `chore` — all additive, none breaking.
+
+## Headline
+
+The ledger money layer gains its arithmetic operations — `addMoney` /
+`subtractMoney` (ADR 0003) — built on the ADR 0002 rounding primitive so sums and
+differences are exact at minor-unit precision. Alongside it, the app adopts the
+"Ruled Ledger" visual v2 identity.
+
+## What's new
+
+- **Money add/subtract arithmetic** (`addMoney` / `subtractMoney`, ADR 0003).
+  Currency-aware add and subtract performed in integer minor-unit space, then
+  canonicalized through `roundMoney` — `0.1 + 0.2` is exactly `0.30` (USD), the
+  IEEE-754 drift never survives the integer round-trip. Operands are bare numbers
+  or currency-tagged `Money`; mixed-currency or non-finite operands throw a typed
+  `MoneyArithmeticError` (extends `RangeError`) rather than corrupting a balance.
+  Pure, side-effect-free, fail-loud. 34 unit tests pass.
+- **"Ruled Ledger" visual v2 identity.** Paper-stock surfaces, ink typography, a
+  single emerald accent, T-account card framing, Fraunces + IBM Plex pairing —
+  applied across the shell, landing, dashboard, and ledger/feature cards. UI-only;
+  no API or behavior change.
+- **Brand assets.** Logo, favicon, and hero background for the new identity.
+
+## Bump rationale (auditable)
+
+| Input | Signal | Bump |
+|-------|--------|------|
+| `feat(ledger): money arithmetic add/subtract (ADR 0003)` (`300e220`) | new backward-compatible API | MINOR |
+| `feat: visual v2 upgrade — "Ruled Ledger" identity` (`885afae`) | UI-only, no API change | PATCH-equiv |
+| `chore: add brand assets` (`d5f670c`) | non-code assets | — |
+| Breaking changes since `v0.3.0`? | none | — |
+
+→ Highest applicable bump = **MINOR** → `0.4.0`.
+
+## Release-integrity gate (cleared)
+
+The `v0.3.0` integrity gate — the barrel `src/features/ledger/index.ts` re-exporting
+then-untracked `amount.ts` / `ingest.ts` — is now **cleared**: those files were
+committed in `3aaf2c9`, and `arithmetic.ts` in `300e220`. All barrel-referenced
+modules are git-tracked. `tsc --noEmit` is clean and the full test suite passes
+(34/34). The previously deferred **`v0.3.0` tag has been cut at `3aaf2c9`** as part
+of this release, and `v0.4.0` is tagged at `300e220`.
+
+## Known issues / carried-over follow-ups
+
+- **`postcss` XSS still open (partial fix)** — GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93 (moderate).
+  The top-level `postcss` is pinned `^8.5.15` (`package.json`), but `next@16.2.6`
+  hard-pins a nested `postcss@8.4.31` (`node_modules/next/node_modules/postcss`)
+  that the direct bump does not reach; `npm audit` reports 2 moderate. The fix is
+  a `package.json` `overrides` block (`"postcss": ">=8.5.10"`) — **not**
+  `npm audit fix --force` (which proposes a breaking `next@9.3.3` downgrade).
+  Build-time CSS stringify only; real-world reachability low. Tracked for the next
+  dependency-maintenance cycle (Security Sentinel scan @ `300e220`).
+- **No `MAX_AMOUNT` bound in `combine()`** (`arithmetic.ts:88`) — `addMoney` /
+  `subtractMoney` accept any finite operand, unlike the `$1M` cap `amount.ts`
+  enforces at the input boundary. Precision-safe today; a future `sumMoney`
+  reducer or an explicit bound should own aggregate-overflow protection. Low /
+  data-integrity, not exploitable.
+- Keep ledger secrets (`GEMINI_API_KEY`, `PLAID_SECRET`, `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN`,
+  `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`) server-side; never `NEXT_PUBLIC_`-prefix them when the
+  adapters are wired.
